name: banking-ms-config
description: This repository has the application configuration files for the banking microservices that can found on the "microservices" project.

name: Microservice-E-commerce-Backend
description: This project contain the microservice approach to develop E-commerce web application. This project contain the different services like product, user, cart, order and all the API gateway as well as the service integration. This project include the backend code only.

name: X-Transact
description: A Microservices based banking application with loans cards and accounts microsoervices.

name: minibank
description: Mini Bank is a microservices-based application that provides a simple banking system with features such as account creation, balance transfer, and account retrieval. The application is designed using a microservices architecture, where each service is responsible for a specific business function.

name: e-commerce-app
description: This repository contains a sample e-commerce application built using the concepts of microservices architecture. The application demonstrates the use of various technologies including Spring Boot, REST API, PostgreSQL, MongoDB, and Docker.

name: Walletify
description: This monorepo houses comprehensive wallet functionality by integrating multiple microservices and full-stack applications for improved scalability. This project enables users to seamlessly manage their digital wallets.

name: base-backend-ASP-NET-Core
description: This repository contains a template for creating a web application using a three-layer architecture, including DataAccess, BusinessLogic, and Presentation layers. All logic is encapsulated in C# class libraries. Controllers are located in ASP.NET Core Web API applications (microservices).
